ZCZC GE01
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 162300 UTC
ON FRIDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE LIES ACROSS
THE N SEA AND ENGLISH CHANNEL WHILE A LARGE DEEP LOW
LIES CENTRED 964 W OF SOLE. OVERNIGHT FRIDAY AND DURING
SATURDAY HIGH PRESSURE PERSISTS ACROSS THE N SEA AND THE
ENGLISH CHANNEL WHILE THE LOW MOVS N AND E CENTRED 965
BAILEY BY SATURDAY EVENING. STRG WINDS DEVELOP ACROSS ALL
AREAS. OVERNIGHT SATURDAY AND DURING SUNDAY THE LOW
CONTINUES TO MOV NE AND BEGINS TO FILL CENTRED 968 N OF
THE FAEROE ISLANDS BY SUNDAY EVENING. HIGH PRESSURE
BEGINS TO DECLINE OVER THE N SEA AND ENGLISH CHANNEL
WITH A SW FLOW BECMG ESTABLISHED AND STRG WINDS
PERSISTING ACROSS ALL AREAS. OVERNIGHT SUNDAY AND DURING
MONDAY THE SW FLOW STRENGTHENS AS HIGH PRESSURE BUILDS
OVER EUROPE WITH STRG WINDS DEVELOPING IN ALL AREAS AND
GALES POSS IN THE N SEA
